    summary: 'From Italian "chiaro" (light) and "oscuro" (dark) — the use of strong tonal contrast to model three-dimensional form. Caravaggio radicalized it into tenebrism: extreme darkness punctured by single spotlit figures. The technique directly shaped cinema — German Expressionist film and film noir owe it an enormous debt.',
    artists: ['Leonardo', 'Caravaggio', 'Rembrandt', 'Goya'],
  },
