    summary: 'Leonardo\'s own term (from "fumo," smoke) for blending oil glazes so gradually that contours dissolve into atmospheric haze. Applied in dozens of near-transparent layers, it creates the mysterious depth of the Mona Lisa\'s smile. Leonardo described it as painting "without lines or borders, in the manner of smoke."',
