    summary: 'Buon fresco applies pigment onto fresh wet lime plaster — as it sets, the pigment bonds chemically into the wall permanently. Michelangelo painted the Sistine ceiling this way over four years, working in daily sections (giornate) before the plaster dried. Well-executed frescoes can outlast millennia.',
    artists: ['Giotto', 'Masaccio', 'Michelangelo', 'Raphael', 'Diego Rivera'],
  },
  {
    category: 'techniques',
    title: 'Impasto',
    subtitle: 'Sculptural Paint',
